{
  "texts": [
    "Ahmad et al.",
    "(32) found that Chemprop performed better than ChemBERTa for ClinTox classification, a drug-toxicity classification task.",
    "However, ChemBERTa was found to perform better than Chemprop on a number of other MoleculeNet benchmark tasks (51), suggesting that either model could be utilized.",
    "Additionally, we compared these models with random and scaffold based train/test split stratification.",
    "OnSIDES: Enabling large-scale, broad studies of ADEs ADEs are a significant cause of morbidity, mortality and unnecessary additional medical treatment worldwide."
  ]
}